ct to the nearest millimetre.\nOne side has a length of 8.2 cm and another has a length of 9.4 cm.\n\nFind the largest possible value of the perimeter of this triangle.\n\n cm","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2020OctNov-Paper22-Q19","paper":"2020OctNov-Paper22","qnum":19,"marks":6,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/20 Q19","year":2020,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Calculate the value of x.\n\n(b) Calculate the area of the triangle.\n\n cm$^2$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"x"}},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2020OctNov-Paper22-Q20","paper":"2020OctNov-Paper22","qnum":20,"marks":3,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.4","d":2,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Surface area and volume","qtype":"surface area and volume","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/20 Q20","year":2020,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A model of a statue has a height of 4 cm.\nThe volume of the model is 12 cm$^3$.\nThe volume of the statue is 40 500 cm$^3$.\n\nCalculate the height of the statue.\n\n cm","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2020OctNov-Paper22-Q21","paper":"2020OctNov-Paper22","qnum":21,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Coordinate geometry"],"s":"2.12","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","qtype":"differentiation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/20 Q21","year":2020,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Differentiate $6 + 4x - x^{2}$.\n\n(b) Find the coordinates of the turning point of the graph of $y = 6 + 4x - x^{2}$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"( , )"}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2020OctNov-Paper22-Q22","paper":"2020OctNov-Paper22","qnum":22,"marks":4,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometr